## Admin Panel CSS Quick Reference

When working with `src/app/(payload)/styles/`:

### File Structure
```
styles/
├── admin.scss              # Main import file
├── _variables.scss         # All theme tokens
├── _mixins.scss           # Reusable patterns
├── _base.scss             # Foundation
└── components/
    ├── _navigation.scss   # Sidebar & nav
    ├── _cards.scss        # Card patterns
    ├── _forms.scss        # Form fields
    ├── _typography.scss   # Text styles
    ├── _buttons.scss      # Button styles
    ├── _badges.scss       # Status badges
    ├── _modals.scss       # Drawers/modals
    └── _spacing.scss      # Layout
```

### Available Mixins
- `@include gradient-border($gradient, $width, $bg-color, $radius)` - Gradient borders
- `@include card-base` - Basic card styling
- `@include card-hover($color, $intensity)` - Card hover effects
- `@include focus-ring($color)` - Input focus states
- `@include hover-glow($color, $lift)` - Glow on hover
- `@include gradient-underline($gradient, $width, $max-width, $height, $glow)` - Heading underlines
- `@include stat-card($type)` - Status cards (success/warning/error/info)
- `@include button-base` - Button foundation

### Available Variables

**Colors**:
- `$admin-accent-primary` (indigo), `$admin-accent-success` (green)
- `$admin-accent-warning` (amber), `$admin-accent-error` (red)
- `$admin-accent-info` (cyan)

**Gradients**:
- `$admin-gradient-primary`, `$admin-gradient-success`
- `$admin-gradient-warning`, `$admin-gradient-error`, `$admin-gradient-info`

**Spacing**: `$spacing-xs` through `$spacing-3xl` (0.25rem to 3rem)

**Radius**: `$radius-sm` through `$radius-pill` (4px to 12px)

**Transitions**: `$transition-fast`, `$transition-normal`, `$transition-slow`

### Common Tasks

**Add new component styles**:
1. Create `components/_my-component.scss`
2. Import in `admin.scss`: `@import './components/my-component';`
3. Use existing variables and mixins

**Add new color**:
1. Add to `_variables.scss` as `rgb()` color
2. Use throughout with `$variable-name` or `rgba($variable-name, 0.5)`

**Add new reusable pattern**:
1. Create mixin in `_mixins.scss`
2. Use `@include mixin-name` where needed
